It&#39;s 99%, the cause is the different column names of &#39;Date&#39;.&lt;br/&gt;
The first statement results in three columns:&lt;br/&gt;

    [ID] [name] [DateIn]
The second one:&lt;br/&gt;

    [ID] [name] [DateOut]

EF maps columns to properties by name, so in the second case it can&#39;t map `DateOut` column to `DateIn`property.&lt;br/&gt;
You need to specify the same name for the `Date` column in both statements. E.g. `DateIn AS [Date]` and `DateOut AS [Date]`. And change the property name in the model accordingly.

